description.narrative:
Indicator 1:
By 2020 achieve environmentally sound management of HCFC chemicals and their wastes throughout their life cycle, in accordance with agreed international frameworks, and significantly reduce their release to air, water and soil in order to minimize their adverse impacts on human health and the environment.

Indicator 2: 
2.1.	Survey of ODS alternatives use in Uzbekistan is available and presented;
2.2.	Data on ODS alternatives use in Uzbekistan is available and integrated into relevant decision-making process;
2.3.	Current regulatory HCFC control framework is improved through a number of proposals developed and provided for Government consideration;
2.4.	Technical capacity of Customs Services on HCFC import and exports is enhanced and special equipment, including samples of refrigerant standards for calibrating gas chromatographs and updating software, is provided;
2.5.	Knowledge and capacity of importers (agents) and environmental inspectors on the use of a newly introduced electronic system of declaring ODS/ODS alternatives import/export is improved;
2.6.	Capacity of the State Customs Committee on storage of seized smuggled ODS/ODS alternatives improved;
2.7.	Customs Committee information exchange and interaction with counterparts in other countries in the region are improved.

Indicator 3:
3.1.	Number of newly established and existing HCFC re-use centers equipped and supported with technical/business planning, and the volume of recycled and reclaimed HCFC; 
3.2.	Number of special servicing equipment provided to companies that move from HCFC based technologies to zero-ODS and low GWP technologies;
3.3.	Number of awareness-raising campaigns on benefits of new technologies, to broaden the project’s positive impacts and exploration of scale-up opportunities in partnership with other-than-GEF funding sources;
3.4.	Number of demonstration projects implemented in public/ commercial facilities sector/training centers;
